text: Discover quiet country living on 2.14 usable acres at 13825 E Bradshaw Road in Dewey Humboldt. This 3 bedroom 2 bath manufactured home offers 1,456 sq ft of updated living space with new vinyl flooring, no carpet, and fresh paint inside and out. The bright eat in kitchen and spacious living room feature a wood burning stove, central air, and double pane windows with blinds already installed.Outside, enjoy panoramic mountain views, a covered deck, enclosed Arizona room, and functional extras like a 15x15 storage shed, a tack house, and an oversized detached 2 car garage. The property is fully enclosed with barbed wire fencing and has plenty of off street and RV parking.Major value upgrades include a solar system with no power bill for the past year, a water filtration system, private well, and septic. This home is zoned R1 70, allowing for horses, chickens, and other farm animals, with easy access to nearby trails. Located in the Lazy River community with no HOA, you're just a short drive to Prescott Valley and minutes from AZ 169.Whether you're looking for a homestead, horse property, or just extra room to spread out, this rural retreat checks all the boxes.No HOA. Solar powered. Room for everything.

text: Breathtaking 9 acre property. NO TAXES! Nestled in the most scenic mountains of North Central Arizona, the Bradshaw's, just outside of Prescott. This incredible 9 acre property with protective Covenant (to ensure that an elegant ''Old West'' environment is maintained), is surrounded by State land and the Prescott National Forest, with miles of hiking and horseback riding trails. One of Yavapai County's most desirable parcels with inspiring mountain views at 6,000 ft. high elevation, is now available! Overlooking the famous ''Big Bug Creek'', where you can still pan for gold from the Henrietta Gold Mine, established in 1892, *CONTINUED IN MORE PUBLIC REMARKSyielding the purest gold in Arizona History, much of it near the surface. Your expansive flat building pad offers underground electric and phone cables installed on your property with a new well, a 3 HP Stainless Steel Pump & solid Stainless Steel Cables. text: Ready for developement 3 parcels totalling 6.25-acre zoned M-2 Industrial property at the prominent intersection of Main Street and State Route 69 in Dewey-Humboldt. More than 1,200 feet of highway frontage and tens of thousands of cars passing daily, it offers unmatched visibility. Westbound or eastbound, drivers have direct turn-lane access, making it one of the most accessible development sites along the corridor. Population is up nearly six percent since 2020, with building permits and values rising faster than state and national averages. ''Opportunity is growing in Yavapai County''! Dewey-Humboldt, once home to Arizona's largest iron smelter, today it is known for Mortimer Farms a regional destination that draws families from across Yavapai and Maricopa Counties.
